7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both D-ID and Opus Clip share a solid foundation of core features including Batch Processing. Where D-ID pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Text To Video and Image To Video and Avatar Talking Head and Voice Over and Api Access, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, Opus Clip uniquely offers Auto Captions and Templates, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, D-ID holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while Opus Clip scores 8/10 overall and 9/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, D-ID offers a more budget-friendly entry point at $5.99/mo, compared to Opus Clip's starting price of $15/mo. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. D-ID's free tier and Opus Clip's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
