b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. D-ID is best suited for developers needing talking head API, quick avatar videos, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Opus Clip, meanwhile, shines for YouTubers repurposing to Shorts/Reels, podcast clipping, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2017, D-ID describes itself as \"Turn photos into talking head videos with AI.\" Opus Clip, established in 2022, positions itself as \"AI turns long videos into viral short clips.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Opus Clip** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean D-ID is a poor choice — far from it. D-ID excels in its own right, particularly for developers needing talking head API and quick avatar videos.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent ai clip selection, go with Opus Clip. If affordable entry price matters more to you, D-ID is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
